{"atom_id":"md_AE_assumptions_a026","file":"domains/AE/assumptions.md","line_start":16,"line_end":16,"parent_section":"4. **Prespecified terms; presence or absence of events**","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"   a. Adverse events are generally collected in 2 different ways, either by recording free text or using a prespecified list of terms. In the latter case, the solicitation of information on specific adverse events may affect the frequency at which they are reported; therefore, the fact that a specific adverse event was solicited may be of interest to reviewers. An AEPRESP value of \"Y\" is used to indicate that the event in AETERM was prespecified on the CRF.","heading_level":0,"sibling_index":0,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_md_v1.1+","ts":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
