{"atom_id":"md_AE_assumptions_a030","file":"domains/AE/assumptions.md","line_start":17,"line_end":17,"parent_section":"4. **Prespecified terms; presence or absence of events**","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"   b. If it is important to know which adverse events from a prespecified list were not reported as well as those that did occur, these data should be submitted in a Findings class dataset such as Findings About Events and Interventions (see Section 6.4, Findings About Events or Interventions). A record should be included in that Findings dataset for each prespecified adverse-event term. Records for adverse events that actually occurred should also exist in the AE dataset with AEPRESP set to \"Y.\"","heading_level":0,"sibling_index":1,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":["Section 6.4"],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_md_v1.1+","ts":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
